&lt;h1 class="relative group">The Meaning of Understanding
&lt;div id="the-meaning-of-understanding" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#the-meaning-of-understanding" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>What do you mean when you say, &amp;ldquo;I understand&amp;rdquo;? Sometimes, you might say, &amp;ldquo;I really understand.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Suppose you have a piece of software code before you, or a philosophical idea is revealed to you (e.g., &amp;ldquo;God is knowledge and infinite, Satyam Jnyanam Anantam Brahma&amp;rdquo;), or you have a document (e.g., project requirements) before you. You have read the document or listened to the idea completely, and now you say, &amp;ldquo;I understand.&amp;rdquo; What does that mean?&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>